news.title: Plan to build residential colonies in Hyderabad’s four corners: Telangana housing minister
news.para: Srinivas Reddy announced that the construction of the much-awaited Indiramma houses will commence before Sankranti festival, with a target to complete about five lakh houses in the first phase and 20 lakh houses in the next four years.

news.title: Maharashtra registration department allocates Rs 21 crore to digitise 2.25 lakh property documents
news.para: The decision comes after the latter department warned about possible damage to these films, currently in cold storage. The documents stored as films span over 58 years of property records.

news.title: Over 61 housing societies served notice for illegal groundwater extraction in Ghaziabad
news.para: According to Srishti Jaiswal, assistant geophysicist at the groundwater department, a complainant wrote a letter to the director, alleging that around 76 societies in the city are extracting groundwater illegally without any NOCs.

news.title: Ventive Hospitality IPO subscribed 9.82 times on last day of offer
news.para: The non-institutional investors subscribed 13.87 times, while the quota for qualified institutional buyers (QIBs) mopped up 9.08 times subscription. Retail individual investors (RIIs) quota received 5.94 times the subscription.

news.title: NFRA slaps Rs 8 lakh penalty on two auditors in DB Realty case
news.para: The order came after NFRA received information from Sebi in October 2022, regarding misstatements in the financial statement of DB Realty Ltd (now known as Valor Estate Ltd).

news.title: Restoration of land cannot be permitted after 12 years: Karnataka HC
news.para: A division bench comprising Chief Justice NV Anjaria and Justice KV Aravind rejected an appeal by M Manjula and others, heirs of late Lakshmaiah, a Scheduled Caste member who received the land grant in 1981.

news.title: BMC issues new guidelines to curb air pollution in Mumbai
news.para: ​​In a release, the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation instructed its solid waste department officials to strictly follow the guidelines, which come in response to growing concerns over deteriorating air quality in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region.

news.title: New home sales in US rise 5.9% in November 2024
news.para: New home sales jumped 5.9% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 664,000 units last month, the Commerce Department's Census Bureau said on Monday.

news.title: Forest department seizes 21 trucks for illegal sand transport in Jorhat
news.para: The trucks were caught carrying sand excavated from the Brahmaputra riverbed in the Kokilamukh area, allegedly destined for a NH construction project

news.title: Vadodara civic body razes illegal portions of bungalow in Tandalja
news.para: Sources said that the bungalow was issued notices in the past too regarding the illegal construction.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body approves 8,440 crore budget for 2025-26 fiscal
news.para: The revenue receipts estimated in the 2024-25 budget were 5,938 crore, which included 1,200 crore of govt grants (compensation to GHMC for debt servicing).

news.title: All developmental works in Amaravati will be completed in three years: Andhra Pradesh minister
news.para: Minister for Municipal Administration and Urban Development (MAUD), Ponguru Narayana said that 7,01,481 TIDCO housing units got sanctioned by the Centre between 2014 and 2019 of which five lakh houses were given administrative sanction while 4,54,706 units have already been grounded.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body urges residents to pay property tax by December 31
news.para: No penalty is imposed on payment of property tax for the current financial year by Dec 31 but a 10% penalty will be imposed on payment of tax after Dec 31.

news.title: Kochi: Amicus Curiae visits Maradu to assess construction limits in demolition site
news.para: The Supreme Court bench led by Justice B R Gavai instructed Agarwal to visit Maradu and prepare the report. Sub-collector K Meera, Maradu municipality chairman Antony Ashamparambil, vice-chairperson Rashmi Sanil, and others accompanied the team.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body to launch portal and impose penalty to curb illegal constructions
news.para: The unauthorised constructions include additional floors, road encroachments, deviation from approved plan, violation of setbacks, building without proper approvals and occupying govt or private land.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to collect property tax from railways
news.para: Previous attempts by HDMC were unsuccessful as railway officials did not provide necessary property details. However, the current initiative received a favourable response from railways authorities.

news.title: Jaipur: Unity Mall project in Fintech Park gets 100 crore sanctioned by finance ministry
news.para: The Union finance ministry already approved the project under a special assistance scheme and sanctioned Rs 100 crore, 50% of the Rs 200 crore allocation, for its construction.

news.title: Hyderabad: Real estate firm accused of duping buyers, CCS takes over probe
news.para: Gupta along with others allegedly collected 5 crore for a fictitious project in Vattinagulapalli. Authorities said Gupta has a history, with 11 cases already registered against him for similar offences.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government allows construction of buildings up to five floors without approval
news.para: The applicants could straight away start the work merely by filing application and payment of prescribed fee to the municipal bodies.
